# Tor configuration for anon-ticket
# This file intentionally disables the local SOCKS listener (SocksPort 0)
# to avoid binding conflicts; the service is expected to run headless.

## General runtime settings
DataDirectory ./tor-data
SocksPort 0
# Optional: expose control via a Unix socket (preferred) for tooling/scripts
ControlSocket ./tor-control.sock
CookieAuthentication 1
CookieAuthFileGroupReadable 1

## Built-in PoW / DoS defenses for onion services
HiddenServiceEnableIntroDoSDefense 1
HiddenServiceStatistics 0

## Hidden Service (placeholder)
# Replace <path> with a persistent directory (must be readable/writable by tor)
HiddenServiceDir ./hidden_service
HiddenServiceVersion 3
# Map virtual port 80 of the onion to your internal listener (example: 127.0.0.1:8080)
HiddenServicePort 80 127.0.0.1:8080
# Add more ports as needed:
# HiddenServicePort 443 127.0.0.1:8443

